15/04/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- A bridge in Kosovo will be rebuilt under the auspices of KFOR, according to the peacekeeping force's Web site.
Kacanik Bridge, about 1km from the town of Kacanik, spanning the Lepenac River, will be demolished on 2 May.
A bypass is already in place to detour traffic.
The reconstruction project is being conducted by the ministry of transportation and communication, the European Agency for Reconstruction and KFOR.
The cost of the project has been estimated at 2.7m euros;
KFOR will cover 20 per cent of that amount.
(KFOR Web site - 14/04/04)
